Habitat. Lentic small water body (reservoir) with brown-reddish water near the Ankazomborona village along Route Nationale 4 at an altitude ca 12 m asl. The area is characterised by the Tropical Savanna Climate ( Köppen 1936 ; Köppen & Geiger 1954 ;
Peel et al . 2007
). Sponges, found along the coastal line of the reservoir periodically subjected to the dry up, were settled in the variably shaded areas on boulders surfaces exposed to air or submerged in shallow water. Sponges were associated with diatoms, and larvae/pupae of insects.
